## 🔑 Why "Molecular Context"?

The name is a metaphor — just like molecules are assembled from atoms, this function assembles a **complete reasoning context** from atomic parts (instruction + examples + new input). Each piece alone is meaningless; combined, they give the model everything it needs to answer correctly.

---

## 📊 Technique Comparison

| Technique | Format Type | When to Use | Accuracy |
|---|---|---|---|
| Zero-shot | No examples at all | Simple, well-known tasks | Baseline |
| **Few-shot** | `input-output` | Pattern matching, translation, classification | Better |
| **Chain-of-Thought** | `chain-of-thought` | Math, reasoning, multi-step logic | Best for complex tasks |

